    "content": "nullExperience Cloud\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Experience Cloud\n Understand the Basics\n Plan & Prepare\n Set Up & Configure\n Manage Users and Data Access\n Build & Customize\n Create Use-Case Driven Sites\n Secure Your Site\n Test & Deploy\n Manage & Moderate\n Managers, Moderators, and Admins Working Together\n Experience Cloud Site Moderation Strategies and Tools\n Organize Experience Cloud Sites with Topics\n Customize Recommendations in Experience Cloud Sites\n Gamification\n Recognition Badges\n Recognition Badges Limitations\n Recognition Badges Setup\n Enable WDC Thanks\n Turn On Recognition Badges in Experience Workspaces\n Configure Who Can Create Recognition Badges\n Configure Who Can Assign Recognition Badges\n Use Components to Display Assigned Recognition Badges on Member...\n Create, Edit, and Delete Recognition Badges\n Manage Who Can Assign a Specific Recognition Badge\n Display the Full List of Assigned Recognition Badges on a Member’s...\n Missions\n Assign Recognition Badges to Experience Cloud Site Members\n Delete Assigned Badges\n Use the API to Give Recognition Badges Sample Code\n Reputation Overview\n Share a Link to Your Experience Cloud Site\n Switch Between Your Salesforce Org and Your Experience Cloud Sites\n Use Reporting in Experience Cloud Sites\n Considerations\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nEXPERIENCE CLOUD\nCreate, Edit, and Delete Recognition Badges\n\nIn addition to the four default badges, you can create your own to fit the needs of your site. You can edit both the default badges and your custom badges.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS\nAvailable in: Enterprise, Professional, Unlimited, and Developer editions.\n\n\nUSER PERMISSIONS NEEDED\nTo create recognition badges:\tCreate Custom Badge Definitions\nTo manage your recognition badges:\t\n\nCreate And Set Up Experiences\n\nAND\n\nModerate Chatter\n\nOR\n\nManage Experiences\n\nAND\n\nModerate Chatter\n\n\nTo manage badges owned by someone else:\t\n\nModify All Data\n\nAND\n\nModerate Chatter\n\nTo create a badge, in Experience Workspaces, click the Gamification tile and go to the Recognition Badges section.\nClick New.\nGive your badge a name and a description and upload an image. Click Save. The Public and Active checkboxes are selected by default. When you save, your badge is immediately available to everyone with permissions to give a badge. If you want to limit who can give a badge, deselect Public. If you aren’t ready for it to be live, deselect Active. If you want the badge to be available for a mission, select Mission Badge.\nTo edit the fields, go to the badge related list, click the dropdown at the end of the badge’s row, and click Edit.\nTo delete a badge, go to the badge related list, click the dropdown at the end of the badge’s row, and click Delete.\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
